cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM 

This paper deals with clustering algorithms and their efficiency in handling large datasets. The paper proposes a distributed and approximated nearest neighbors algorithm for efficient clustering, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes a scalable procedure for approximating density gradient ascent, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and data mining, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining) likely sub-categories as well.
